---
import SiteLayout from "@/layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
	title="About"
	description="Klustered — the live Kubernetes troubleshooting game show."
>
	<section class="pt-12">
		<p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-fuchsia-400">
			About
		</p>
		<h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
			A game show for broken clusters.
		</h1>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10 grid gap-10 text-slate-300 md:grid-cols-2">
		<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-base">
			<p>
				Klustered started as a live stream in 2021 with a simple premise:
				take working Kubernetes clusters, break them on purpose, and ask real
				engineers to fix them on stage in under an hour.
			</p>
			<p>
				No editing. No retries. The cluster is sabotaged by someone the
				competitor has never met — and the audience watches the debugging
				live.
			</p>
			<p>
				It's part competition, part education. Every fix becomes a master
				class in Kubernetes internals, and every miss teaches the audience
				what to look for next time.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div
			class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-br from-fuchsia-500/15 to-cyan-500/10 p-8"
		>
			<h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-fuchsia-200">
				The format
			</h2>
			<ul class="mt-4 flex flex-col gap-3 text-sm">
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="mt-1 font-mono text-fuchsia-300">01</span>
					<span>
						<strong class="text-white">A working cluster</strong> is provisioned
						and shared with a saboteur.
					</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="mt-1 font-mono text-fuchsia-300">02</span>
					<span>
						<strong class="text-white">Sabotage happens.</strong> Anywhere from
						control plane to admission controllers.
					</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="mt-1 font-mono text-fuchsia-300">03</span>
					<span>
						<strong class="text-white">The competitor takes the kubeconfig</strong>
						and has 60 minutes to restore service.
					</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="mt-1 font-mono text-fuchsia-300">04</span>
					<span>
						<strong class="text-white">The post-mortem</strong> happens live
						on air — the saboteur explains the puzzle, the competitor explains
						the path.
					</span>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>
</SiteLayout>
